result.execSummary:
The defendant Terrance M McClinton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Amending Judgment of Conviction signed, filed and distributed.
Per order of the Presiding Judge, Misdemeanor Division, this motion/request is hereby assigned to the Hon. Michael J. Hanrahan, Br. 4, calendar successor, for review. spc
Letter from DOC requesting review of defendant's sentence credit.

Defendant Terrance M McClinton in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Defendant Terrance M McClinton in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Court sentenced defendant to serve 3 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for 1 day served; Huber privileges for work.  

Court ordered defendant to pay ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by 01-05-2017 or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Court ordered the defendant to submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Attorney Terese M. Dick in court, defendant Terrance M McClinton not in court, in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Defense requests an adjourned Plea and Sentencing date. Court grants defense request.  Parties are advised that effective December 14, 2015, this case will be assigned to the Reserve Judge presiding in Branch 21 in room 622 of the Courthouse. Case adjourned to branch 21.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for January 5, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
